<br>
When you hit something that is yellow to you, you hit it LESS hard then when you hit something that is even. When you hit something that is even, you hit it LESS hard then you hit something that is blue. When you hit something that is blue, you hit it LESS hard then you hit something that is green. Likewise, if you are yellow or red to a mob, it will hit you LESS hard then if you are even or blue to it. When taunting, YOU CAN NOT TAUNT ANYTHING ABOVE YOUR LEVEL, so obviously level DOES matter. As well, here is a copy of the devs talking about the fact that the higher LEVEL you are (not skill) the better you taunt via a new scale method they introduced with the taunt upgrade: <br>
<br>
&quot;Right now Taunt seems to take a second place to Enraging Blow items – is this intended? <br>
<br>
Taunt has been reviewed and should work much better now, on any NPC level, and have a sane progression up to the characters’ 65th level. We are aware that the Enraging Blow items are subjugating the Taunt Skill and we will be looking into this. We don’t particularly like when abilities are obsoleted by items. Enraging Blow items were a temporary fix for a systems problem that has unfortunately stuck around too long. <br>
<br>
We’d much rather have character skills make more sense. Please check out Taunt again as you progress – It now has a much better chance of working for PoP-level players vs PoP-level NPCs.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, to sum up, your damage, the damage you take and the mobs you can taunt are all DIRECTLY related to your level vs the level of the mob. End of story. No question, no supposition, this is FACT. <br>
<br>
That said, it's all about fun. A lot of people have said that so far, and that's really the bottom line of this discussion. But if you want to talk about fun, I enjoy getting an AA every 75 minutes a lot more then grinding one out for 3 hours. And I do, every day, without fail, in groups of even 5 or sometimes a very uber 4, get an AA every 75 minutes. It's not even a difficult thing to do. Do your trials, get your levels and the AA will flow like urine from a drunken dwarf. <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>
