<br>
Did you even read the previous posts?  Level DOES make a big difference.  Level increases HPS, increases your chance to hit, increases your damage output, decreases your aggro radius, increases your resist chance (even with low resist gear on), decreases mob hit and damage rate (independent of AC).  Some of the AAs have a significant effect but aside from AE taunt I challenge you to come up with ANY AA ability that makes as much difference as an added level.<br>
<br>
If you don't believe it take a warrior just high enough level that their skills are capped (don't remember what level this is) and compare their tanking ability to a level 65 warrior.  If you want the difference to be glaringly obvious have them tank a level 65 mob.  I guarantee that the lower level warrior will tank like a wet paper bag compared to the 65.  You can even give the lower level warrior superior buffs so they come out to the same HPs.  The 65 will still EASILY out tank them.  The difference is obviously smaller if there's only 1 level difference but it scales proportionally. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
