No, Haas...  Level is a much larger impact than you wish to believe.  Indeed, if we were to put level as a ratio or as a comparison, you would likely br much closer to the truth.<br>
<br>
EQ is about comparisons...<br>
<br>
First it compares your level and the mob's level and creates some sort of modifier.<br>
<br>
Then it takes ATK (tohit/dampotential) and AC (avoid/mitigation) and compares them.<br>
<br>
Mobs do no have &quot;skills&quot; as you do.  Your skills are a factor in your ATK and AC... only skills such as taunt and Riposte and Parry and Dodge are rolled separately.. and I bet even those have some sort of level based modifier.<br>
<br>
Take your 60th warrior and beat on a greenie... notice the greenie barely touches you and you hand the greenie its butt.  As mobs grow closer in level to you, they deal more damage and you don't ignore their armor.<br>
<br>
Now take you fully buffed warrior and try beating on an even con or higher... I betcha it hurts you something fierce.<br>
<br>
This advantage happens for characters as well.<br>
<br>
Take your 60war and stand-up duel a 65 warrior nekkid ( I'll bet the higher warrior hands you your butt so to speak. (yeah yeah, its slow, but should be decisive if you are same race, same class)<br>
<br>
The level DIFFERENCE modifier is why level&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;AAXP.<br>
<br>
Its more than Haas wants to see.... if 60 with 50AAXP isnt better than 65 with 5, then the modifier is quite a deal...  think of what you could buy with 45 extra AAXP.<br>
<br>
